    {
      "parameters": {
        "modelId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "gpt-4o-mini-search-preview",
          "mode": "list"
        },
        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "You are a B2B go-to-market research analyst. Given a company name, you find structured data about the company, its CEO/founder, AND its sales motion — specifically WHO the company sells to and WHY reaching those buyers at scale is hard. This research feeds a cold-outreach system that pitches custom AI SDR builds, so the GTM fields (ICP, Pain_point, Hook, Founder_detail) are the most important. Be accurate and specific — never vague, never generic. Prefer real, verifiable detail. When a fact is genuinely unavailable, make a well-reasoned inference from the company's category, stage, and product rather than leaving a field blank — but never fabricate a specific named fact (like a person, date, or dollar figure) you cannot support.",
              "role": "system"
            },
            {
              "content": "=Research this company and return structured GTM intelligence:\n\nCompany name: {{ $json[\"Organization_name\"] }}\n\nReturn STRICTLY as JSON (no markdown, no extra text). Every field must have a value — never return an empty string. If a fact is unavailable, infer a sensible value from the company's category, stage, and product (but never fabricate a specific named person, date, or dollar amount). Include the original input value as Organization_name in the returned JSON:\n{\n  \"Organization_name\": \"{{ $json[\"Organization_name\"] }}\",\n  \"Domain\": \"company website domain e.g. acme.com\",\n  \"CEO_First_name\": \"first name of CEO or founder\",\n  \"CEO_Last_name\": \"last name of CEO or founder\",\n  \"CEO_LinkedIn\": \"full linkedin.com/in/... URL of CEO\",\n  \"Description\": \"1-2 sentences: what the company does and the value it delivers\",\n  \"City\": \"city of HQ\",\n  \"Country\": \"country of HQ\",\n  \"Last_funding_type\": \"e.g. Series A, Seed, Series B\",\n  \"Last_funding_date\": \"YYYY-MM-DD format\",\n  \"ICP\": \"THE most important field. Who this company SELLS TO. Be concrete and specific: buyer job titles + the type of company or person that buys. e.g. 'VPs of Engineering and CTOs at Series A-C SaaS startups' or 'independent landlords managing 5-50 rental units' or 'heads of compliance at mid-market banks'. This is who Erica's AI SDR would target on their behalf.\",\n  \"Pain_point\": \"The specific go-to-market / customer-acquisition challenge this company faces in REACHING its ICP — the problem a tailored AI SDR would solve. e.g. 'their buyers are senior, niche and not reachable via ads, so they rely on slow manual 1:1 outreach' or 'long enterprise sales cycles with hard-to-identify decision makers'. Tie it to their actual buyer and motion.\",\n  \"Hook\": \"one specific, non-obvious, verifiable detail about the company useful for cold outreach. NOT a restatement of Description. e.g. a standout metric, an unusual origin, a notable customer, a record-setting raise.\",\n  \"Founder_detail\": \"one specific, memorable detail about the founder useful for personalization. e.g. a prior exit, published research, a public stance, an unusual background or path.\",\n  \"Product_type\": \"one of: SaaS, Marketplace, API/Infrastructure, Hardware, Professional Services, Consumer App, or Data/Analytics — pick the single best fit for this company\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
